A vintage 1950s-style travel poster composition showing a stylized globe with dotted airline routes connecting glowing nodes across continents - Asia, Europe, Australia, and the Americas. Small retro-futuristic workshop buildings with distinctive mid-century modern architecture sit at each connection point, emanating warm golden light. The color palette features muted teals, warm oranges, and cream tones with subtle paper texture overlay. The perspective is slightly tilted, giving dynamic energy to the international network spreading across the curved Earth surface. Silhouettes of small figures gather at each illuminated hub, suggesting collaborative learning moments happening simultaneously worldwide.
